  </div><section class=3D"notoc introductory" id=3D"abstract"><h2>What is t=
he OpenAPI Specification?</h2>The OpenAPI Specification (OAS) defines a sta=
ndard, programming language-agnostic interface description for HTTP APIs, w=
hich allows both humans and computers to discover and understand the capabi=
lities of a service without requiring access to source code, additional doc=
umentation, or inspection of network traffic. When properly defined via Ope=
nAPI, a consumer can understand and interact with the remote service with a=
 minimal amount of implementation logic. Similar to what interface descript=
ions have done for lower-level programming, the OpenAPI Specification remov=
es guesswork in calling a service.</section><section class=3D"override intr=
