=3D"x1-openapi-specification"><bdi class=3D"secno">1. </bdi>OpenAPI Specifi=
cation</h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.=
0.3.html#openapi-specification" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 1."></a=
></div>
<section class=3D"override" id=3D"conformance"><div class=3D"header-wrapper=
"><h3 id=3D"x1-1-version-3-0-3"><bdi class=3D"secno">1.1 </bdi>Version 3.0.=
3</h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.h=
tml#conformance" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 1.1"></a></div>
<p>The key words =E2=80=9C<em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em>=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=
=9C<em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST NOT</em>=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9C<em class=3D"rfc2=
119">REQUIRED</em>=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9C<em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em>=E2=
=80=9D, =E2=80=9C<em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL NOT</em>=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9C<e=
m class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em>=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9C<em class=3D"rfc2119">SH=
OULD NOT</em>=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9C<em class=3D"rfc2119">RECOMMENDED</em>=E2=
=80=9D, =E2=80=9C<em class=3D"rfc2119">NOT RECOMMENDED</em>=E2=80=9D, =E2=
=80=9C<em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em>=E2=80=9D, and =E2=80=9C<em class=3D"rf=
c2119">OPTIONAL</em>=E2=80=9D in this document are to be interpreted as des=
cribed in <a href=3D"https://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp14">BCP 14</a> [<cite><=
a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.=
org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc2119" title=3D"Key words for use in RFCs to Indi=
cate Requirement Levels">RFC2119</a></cite>] [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" dat=
a-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bi=
b-rfc8174" title=3D"Ambiguity of Uppercase vs Lowercase in RFC 2119 Key Wor=
ds">RFC8174</a></cite>] when, and only when, they appear in all capitals, a=
s shown here.</p>
<p>This document is licensed under <a href=3D"https://www.apache.org/licens=
es/LICENSE-2.0.html">The Apache License, Version 2.0</a>.</p>
</section></section><section id=3D"introduction"><div class=3D"header-wrapp=
er"><h2 id=3D"x2-introduction"><bdi class=3D"secno">2. </bdi>Introduction</=
h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html=
#introduction" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 2."></a></div>
<p>The OpenAPI Specification (OAS) defines a standard, language-agnostic in=
terface to RESTful APIs which allows both humans and computers to discover =
and understand the capabilities of the service without access to source cod=
e, documentation, or through network traffic inspection. When properly defi=
ned, a consumer can understand and interact with the remote service with a =
minimal amount of implementation logic.</p>
<p>An OpenAPI definition can then be used by documentation generation tools=
 to display the API, code generation tools to generate servers and clients =
in various programming languages, testing tools, and many other use cases.<=
/p>
</section><section id=3D"definitions"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h2 id=
=3D"x3-definitions"><bdi class=3D"secno">3. </bdi><dfn id=3D"dfn-definition=
s" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Definition=
s</dfn></h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3=
.0.3.html#definitions" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3."></a></div>
<section id=3D"openapi-document"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x3=
-1-openapi-document"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.1 </bdi><dfn id=3D"dfn-openapi-=
document" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Ope=
nAPI Document</dfn></h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapi=
s.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#openapi-document" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section=
 3.1"></a></div>
<p>A document (or set of documents) that defines or describes an API. An Op=
enAPI definition uses and conforms to the OpenAPI Specification.</p>
</section><section id=3D"path-templating"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h3=
 id=3D"x3-2-path-templating"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.2 </bdi><dfn id=3D"dfn-=
path-templating" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"d=
fn">Path Templating</dfn></h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.o=
penapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#path-templating" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Se=
ction 3.2"></a></div>
<p>Path templating refers to the usage of template expressions, delimited b=
y curly braces ({}), to mark a section of a URL path as replaceable using p=
ath parameters.</p>
<p>Each template expression in the path <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> cor=
respond to a path parameter that is included in the <a href=3D"https://spec=
.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#path-item-object">Path Item</a> itself and/or=
 in each of the Path Item=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oa=
s/v3.0.3.html#operation-object">Operations</a>.</p>
</section><section id=3D"media-types"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=
=3D"x3-3-media-types"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.3 </bdi><dfn id=3D"dfn-media-t=
ypes" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Media T=
ypes</dfn></h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas=
/v3.0.3.html#media-types" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3.3"></a></di=
v>
<p>Media type definitions are spread across several resources.
The media type definitions <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> be in complian=
ce with [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https:=
//spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc6838" title=3D"Media Type Specif=
ications and Registration Procedures">RFC6838</a></cite>].</p>
<p>Some examples of possible media type definitions:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code>  text/plain; charset=3Dutf=
-8
  application/json
  application/vnd.github+json
  application/vnd.github.v3+json
  application/vnd.github.v3.raw+json
  application/vnd.github.v3.text+json
  application/vnd.github.v3.html+json
  application/vnd.github.v3.full+json
  application/vnd.github.v3.diff
  application/vnd.github.v3.patch
</code></pre>
</section><section id=3D"http-status-codes"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><=
h3 id=3D"x3-4-http-status-codes"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.4 </bdi><dfn id=3D"=
dfn-http-status-codes" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-typ=
e=3D"dfn">HTTP Status Codes</dfn></h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https:=
//spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#http-status-codes" aria-label=3D"Permal=
ink for Section 3.4"></a></div>
<p>The HTTP Status Codes are used to indicate the status of the executed op=
eration.
The available status codes are defined by [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-l=
ink-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-r=
fc7231" title=3D"Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP/1.1): Semantics and Cont=
ent">RFC7231</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/r=
fc7231#section-6">Section 6</a> and registered status codes are listed in t=
he <cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec=
.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-iana-http-status-codes" title=3D"Hypertex=
t Transfer Protocol (HTTP) Status Code Registry">IANA Status Code Registry<=
/a></cite>.</p>
</section></section><section id=3D"specification"><div class=3D"header-wrap=
per"><h2 id=3D"x4-specification"><bdi class=3D"secno">4. </bdi>Specificatio=
n</h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.h=
tml#specification" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4."></a></div>
<section id=3D"versions"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x4-1-versi=
ons"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.1 </bdi>Versions</h3><a class=3D"self-link" hre=
f=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#versions" aria-label=3D"Perm=
alink for Section 4.1"></a></div>
<p>The OpenAPI Specification is versioned using <a href=3D"https://semver.o=
rg/spec/v2.0.0.html">Semantic Versioning 2.0.0</a> (semver) and follows the=
 semver specification.</p>
<p>The <code>major</code>.<code>minor</code> portion of the semver (for exa=
mple <code>3.0</code>) <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> designate the OAS f=
eature set. Typically, <em><code>.patch</code></em> versions address errors=
 in this document, not the feature set. Tooling which supports OAS 3.0 <em =
class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> be compatible with all OAS 3.0.* versions. Th=
e patch version <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD NOT</em> be considered by tool=
ing, making no distinction between <code>3.0.0</code> and <code>3.0.1</code=
> for example.</p>
<p>Each new minor version of the OpenAPI Specification <em class=3D"rfc2119=
">SHALL</em> allow any OpenAPI document that is valid against any previous =
minor version of the Specification, within the same major version, to be up=
dated to the new Specification version with equivalent semantics. Such an u=
pdate <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> only require changing the <code>opena=
pi</code> property to the new minor version.</p>
<p>For example, a valid OpenAPI 3.0.2 document, upon changing its <code>ope=
napi</code> property to <code>3.1.0</code>, <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em=
> be a valid OpenAPI 3.1.0 document, semantically equivalent to the origina=
l OpenAPI 3.0.2 document. New minor versions of the OpenAPI Specification <=
em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be written to ensure this form of backward c=
ompatibility.</p>
<p>An OpenAPI document compatible with OAS 3.*.* contains a required <a hre=
f=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#oasVersion"><code>openapi</c=
ode></a> field which designates the semantic version of the OAS that it use=
s. (OAS 2.0 documents contain a top-level version field named <a href=3D"ht=
tps://github.com/OAI/OpenAPI-Specification/blob/master/versions/2.0.md#swag=
gerObject"><code>swagger</code></a> and value <code>"2.0"</code>.)</p>
</section><section id=3D"format"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x4=
-2-format"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.2 </bdi>Format</h3><a class=3D"self-link"=
 href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#format" aria-label=3D"Pe=
rmalink for Section 4.2"></a></div>
<p>An OpenAPI document that conforms to the OpenAPI Specification is itself=
 a JSON object, which may be represented either in <cite><a class=3D"bibref=
" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.ht=
ml#bib-rfc7159" title=3D"The JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) Data Interch=
ange Format">JSON</a></cite> or <cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D=
"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-yaml" title=
=3D"YAML Ain=E2=80=99t Markup Language (YAML=E2=84=A2) Version 1.2">YAML</a=
></cite> format.</p>
<p>For example, if a field has an array value, the JSON array representatio=
n will be used:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-punctua=
tion">{</span>
   <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"field"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation"=
>:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">[</span> <span class=3D"hljs-num=
ber">1</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">,</span> <span class=3D"hljs-=
number">2</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">,</span> <span class=3D"hl=
js-number">3</span> <span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">]</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre>
<p>All field names in the specification are <strong>case sensitive</strong>=
.
This includes all fields that are used as keys in a map, except where expli=
citly noted that keys are <strong>case insensitive</strong>.</p>
<p>The schema exposes two types of fields: Fixed fields, which have a decla=
red name, and Patterned fields, which declare a regex pattern for the field=
 name.</p>
<p>Patterned fields <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> have unique names withi=
n the containing object.</p>
<p>In order to preserve the ability to round-trip between YAML and JSON for=
mats, <cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://s=
pec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-yaml" title=3D"YAML Ain=E2=80=99t Mark=
up Language (YAML=E2=84=A2) Version 1.2">YAML version 1.2</a></cite> is <em=
 class=3D"rfc2119">RECOMMENDED</em> along with some additional constraints:=
</p>
<ul>
<li>Tags <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be limited to those allowed by the=
 <a href=3D"https://yaml.org/spec/1.2/spec.html#id2803231">JSON Schema rule=
set</a>.</li>
<li>Keys used in YAML maps <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be limited to a =
scalar string, as defined by the <a href=3D"https://yaml.org/spec/1.2/spec.=
html#id2802346">YAML Failsafe schema ruleset</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> While APIs may be defined by OpenAPI documents in=
 either YAML or JSON format, the API request and response bodies and other =
content are not required to be JSON or YAML.</p>
</section><section id=3D"document-structure"><div class=3D"header-wrapper">=
<h3 id=3D"x4-3-document-structure"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.3 </bdi>Document =
Structure</h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/=
v3.0.3.html#document-structure" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.3"></=
a></div>
<p>An OpenAPI document <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be made up of a singl=
e document or be divided into multiple, connected parts at the discretion o=
f the user. In the latter case, <code>$ref</code> fields <em class=3D"rfc21=
19">MUST</em> be used in the specification to reference those parts as foll=
ows from the <a href=3D"https://json-schema.org/">JSON Schema</a> definitio=
ns.</p>
<p>It is <em class=3D"rfc2119">RECOMMENDED</em> that the root OpenAPI docum=
ent be named: <code>openapi.json</code> or <code>openapi.yaml</code>.</p>
</section><section id=3D"data-types"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=
=3D"x4-4-data-types"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.4 </bdi>Data Types</h3><a class=
=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#data-types=
" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.4"></a></div>
<p>Primitive data types in the OAS are based on the types supported by the =
<a href=3D"https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-wright-json-schema-00#section-=
4.2">JSON Schema Specification Wright Draft 00</a>.
Note that <code>integer</code> as a type is also supported and is defined a=
s a JSON number without a fraction or exponent part.
<code>null</code> is not supported as a type (see <a href=3D"https://spec.o=
penapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#schemaNullable"><code>nullable</code></a> for a=
n alternative solution).
Models are defined using the <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.=
3.html#schema-object">Schema Object</a>, which is an extended subset of JSO=
N Schema Specification Wright Draft 00.</p>
<p><span id=3D"dataTypeFormat"></span>Primitives have an optional modifier =
property: <code>format</code>.
OAS uses several known formats to define in fine detail the data type being=
 used.
However, to support documentation needs, the <code>format</code> property i=
s an open <code>string</code>-valued property, and can have any value.
Formats such as <code>"email"</code>, <code>"uuid"</code>, and so on, <em c=
lass=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be used even though undefined by this specificati=
on.
Types that are not accompanied by a <code>format</code> property follow the=
 type definition in the JSON Schema. Tools that do not recognize a specific=
 <code>format</code> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> default back to the <co=
de>type</code> alone, as if the <code>format</code> is not specified.</p>
<p>The formats defined by the OAS are:</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th><a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#data-types"><code>=
type</code></a></th>
<th><a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#dataTypeFormat"><c=
ode>format</code></a></th>
<th>Comments</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>integer</code></td>
<td><code>int32</code></td>
<td>signed 32 bits</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>integer</code></td>
<td><code>int64</code></td>
<td>signed 64 bits (a.k.a long)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>number</code></td>
<td><code>float</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>number</code></td>
<td><code>double</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>string</code></td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>string</code></td>
<td><code>byte</code></td>
<td>base64 encoded characters</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>string</code></td>
<td><code>binary</code></td>
<td>any sequence of octets</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>boolean</code></td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>string</code></td>
<td><code>date</code></td>
<td>As defined by <code>full-date</code> - [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-=
link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-=
rfc3339" title=3D"Date and Time on the Internet: Timestamps">RFC3339</a></c=
ite>] <a href=3D"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc3339#section-5.6"=
>Section 5.6</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>string</code></td>
<td><code>date-time</code></td>
<td>As defined by <code>date-time</code> - [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-=
link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-=
rfc3339" title=3D"Date and Time on the Internet: Timestamps">RFC3339</a></c=
ite>] <a href=3D"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc3339#section-5.6"=
>Section 5.6</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>string</code></td>
<td><code>password</code></td>
<td>A hint to UIs to obscure input.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</section><section id=3D"rich-text-formatting"><div class=3D"header-wrapper=
"><h3 id=3D"x4-5-rich-text-formatting"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.5 </bdi>Rich =
Text Formatting</h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.or=
g/oas/v3.0.3.html#rich-text-formatting" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section=
 4.5"></a></div>
<p>Throughout the specification <code>description</code> fields are noted a=
s supporting [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-commonmark" title=3D"CommonMar=
k Spec">CommonMark</a></cite>] markdown formatting.
Where OpenAPI tooling renders rich text it <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> =
support, at a minimum, markdown syntax as described by [<cite><a class=3D"b=
ibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0=
.3.html#bib-commonmark-0.27" title=3D"CommonMark Spec, Version 0.27">Common=
Mark-0.27</a></cite>]. Tooling <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> choose to ign=
ore some CommonMark features to address security concerns.</p>
</section><section id=3D"relative-references-in-urls"><div class=3D"header-=
wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x4-6-relative-references-in-urls"><bdi class=3D"secno">4=
.6 </bdi>Relative References in URLs</h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"htt=
ps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#relative-references-in-urls" aria-la=
bel=3D"Permalink for Section 4.6"></a></div>
<p>Unless specified otherwise, all properties that are URLs <em class=3D"rf=
c2119">MAY</em> be relative references as defined by [<cite><a class=3D"bib=
ref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3=
.html#bib-rfc3986" title=3D"Uniform Resource Identifier (URI): Generic Synt=
ax">RFC3986</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rf=
c3986#section-4.2">Section 4.2</a>.
Relative references are resolved using the URLs defined in the <a href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#server-object"><code>Server Object=
</code></a> as a Base URI.</p>
<p>Relative references used in <code>$ref</code> are processed as per <cite=
><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapi=
s.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-json-reference" title=3D"JSON Reference">JSON Ref=
erence</a></cite>, using the URL of the current document as the base URI. S=
ee also the <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#reference-=
object">Reference Object</a>.</p>
