le</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.=
html#external-documentation-object-example" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Sec=
tion 4.7.11.2"></a></div>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-punctua=
tion">{</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"description"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctua=
tion">:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"Find more info here"</span><spa=
n class=3D"hljs-punctuation">,</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"url"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">:<=
/span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"https://example.com"</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">d=
escription:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">Find</span> <span class=3D"h=
ljs-string">more</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">info</span> <span class=
=3D"hljs-string">here</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-attr">url:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">https://e=
xample.com</span>
</code></pre>
</section></section><section id=3D"parameter-object"><div class=3D"header-w=
rapper"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-12-parameter-object"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.12 </b=
di>Parameter Object</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapi=
s.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameter-object" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section=
 4.7.12"></a></div>
<p>Describes a single operation parameter.</p>
<p>A unique parameter is defined by a combination of a <a href=3D"https://s=
pec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameterName">name</a> and <a href=3D"htt=
ps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameterIn">location</a>.</p>
<section id=3D"parameter-locations"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D=
"x4-7-12-1-parameter-locations"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.12.1 </bdi>Paramet=
er Locations</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/o=
as/v3.0.3.html#parameter-locations" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7=
.12.1"></a></div>
<p>There are four possible parameter locations specified by the <code>in</c=
ode> field:</p>
<ul>
<li>path - Used together with <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0=
.3.html#path-templating">Path Templating</a>, where the parameter value is =
actually part of the operation=E2=80=99s URL. This does not include the hos=
t or base path of the API. For example, in <code>/items/{itemId}</code>, th=
e path parameter is <code>itemId</code>.</li>
<li>query - Parameters that are appended to the URL. For example, in <code>=
/items?id=3D###</code>, the query parameter is <code>id</code>.</li>
<li>header - Custom headers that are expected as part of the request. Note =
that [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://s=
pec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc7230" title=3D"Hypertext Transfer P=
rotocol (HTTP/1.1): Message Syntax and Routing">RFC7230</a></cite>] <a href=
=3D"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7230#page-22">Page 22</a> stat=
es header names are case insensitive.</li>
<li>cookie - Used to pass a specific cookie value to the API.</li>
</ul>
</section><section id=3D"fixed-fields-9"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 =
id=3D"x4-7-12-2-fixed-fields"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.12.2 </bdi>Fixed Fie=
lds</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3=
.html#fixed-fields-9" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.12.2"></a></d=
iv>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterName"></span>name</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. The name of the p=
arameter. Parameter names are <em>case sensitive</em>. <ul><li>If <a href=
=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameterIn"><code>in</code><=
/a> is <code>"path"</code>, the <code>name</code> field <em class=3D"rfc211=
9">MUST</em> correspond to a template expression occurring within the <a hr=
ef=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#pathsPath">path</a> field i=
n the <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#paths-object">Pa=
ths Object</a>. See <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#pa=
th-templating">Path Templating</a> for further information.</li><li>If <a h=
ref=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameterIn"><code>in</cod=
e></a> is <code>"header"</code> and the <code>name</code> field is <code>"A=
ccept"</code>, <code>"Content-Type"</code> or <code>"Authorization"</code>,=
 the parameter definition <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> be ignored.</li>=
<li>For all other cases, the <code>name</code> corresponds to the parameter=
 name used by the <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#para=
meterIn"><code>in</code></a> property.</li></ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterIn"></span>in</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. The location of t=
he parameter. Possible values are <code>"query"</code>, <code>"header"</cod=
e>, <code>"path"</code> or <code>"cookie"</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterDescription"></span>description</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>A brief description of the parameter. This could contain examples of us=
e. [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spe=
c.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-commonmark" title=3D"CommonMark Spec">Co=
mmonMark</a></cite>] syntax <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be used for rich=
 text representation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterRequired"></span>required</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>boolean</code></td>
<td>Determines whether this parameter is mandatory. If the <a href=3D"https=
://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameterIn">parameter location</a> is=
 <code>"path"</code>, this property is <strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIR=
ED</em></strong> and its value <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be <code>tru=
e</code>. Otherwise, the property <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be include=
d and its default value is <code>false</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterDeprecated"></span> deprecated</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>boolean</code></td>
<td>Specifies that a parameter is deprecated and <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOU=
LD</em> be transitioned out of usage. Default value is <code>false</code>.<=
/td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterAllowEmptyValue"></span> allowEmptyValue</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>boolean</code></td>
<td>Sets the ability to pass empty-valued parameters. This is valid only fo=
r <code>query</code> parameters and allows sending a parameter with an empt=
y value. Default value is <code>false</code>. If <a href=3D"https://spec.op=
enapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameterStyle"><code>style</code></a> is used, =
and if behavior is <code>n/a</code> (cannot be serialized), the value of <c=
ode>allowEmptyValue</code> <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> be ignored. Use=
 of this property is <em class=3D"rfc2119">NOT RECOMMENDED</em>, as it is l=
ikely to be removed in a later revision.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>The rules for serialization of the parameter are specified in one of two=
 ways.
For simpler scenarios, a <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.ht=
ml#parameterSchema"><code>schema</code></a> and <a href=3D"https://spec.ope=
napis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameterStyle"><code>style</code></a> can descri=
be the structure and syntax of the parameter.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterStyle"></span>style</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>Describes how the parameter value will be serialized depending on the t=
ype of the parameter value. Default values (based on value of <code>in</cod=
e>): for <code>query</code> - <code>form</code>; for <code>path</code> - <c=
ode>simple</code>; for <code>header</code> - <code>simple</code>; for <code=
>cookie</code> - <code>form</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterExplode"></span>explode</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>boolean</code></td>
<td>When this is true, parameter values of type <code>array</code> or <code=
>object</code> generate separate parameters for each value of the array or =
key-value pair of the map. For other types of parameters this property has =
no effect. When <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parame=
terStyle"><code>style</code></a> is <code>form</code>, the default value is=
 <code>true</code>. For all other styles, the default value is <code>false<=
/code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterAllowReserved"></span>allowReserved</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>boolean</code></td>
<td>Determines whether the parameter value <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em=
> allow reserved characters, as defined by [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-=
link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-=
rfc3986" title=3D"Uniform Resource Identifier (URI): Generic Syntax">RFC398=
6</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc3986#sect=
ion-2.2">Section 2.2</a> <code>:/?#[]@!$&amp;'()*+,;=3D</code> to be includ=
ed without percent-encoding. This property only applies to parameters with =
an <code>in</code> value of <code>query</code>. The default value is <code>=
false</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterSchema"></span>schema</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3=
.0.3.html#schema-object">Schema Object</a> | <a href=3D"https://spec.openap=
is.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#reference-object">Reference Object</a></td>
<td>The schema defining the type used for the parameter.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterExample"></span>example</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center">Any</td>
<td>Example of the parameter=E2=80=99s potential value. The example <em cla=
ss=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> match the specified schema and encoding properti=
es if present. The <code>example</code> field is mutually exclusive of the =
<code>examples</code> field. Furthermore, if referencing a <code>schema</co=
de> that contains an example, the <code>example</code> value <em class=3D"r=
fc2119">SHALL</em> <em>override</em> the example provided by the schema. To=
 represent examples of media types that cannot naturally be represented in =
JSON or YAML, a string value can contain the example with escaping where ne=
cessary.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterExamples"></span>examples</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center">Map[ <code>string</code>, <a href=3D"https:=
//spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#example-object">Example Object</a> | <a=
 href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#reference-object">Refere=
nce Object</a>]</td>
<td>Examples of the parameter=E2=80=99s potential value. Each example <em c=
lass=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> contain a value in the correct format as speci=
fied in the parameter encoding. The <code>examples</code> field is mutually=
 exclusive of the <code>example</code> field. Furthermore, if referencing a=
 <code>schema</code> that contains an example, the <code>examples</code> va=
lue <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> <em>override</em> the example provided=
 by the schema.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>For more complex scenarios, the <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas=
/v3.0.3.html#parameterContent"><code>content</code></a> property can define=
 the media type and schema of the parameter.
A parameter <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> contain either a <code>schema</=
code> property, or a <code>content</code> property, but not both.
When <code>example</code> or <code>examples</code> are provided in conjunct=
ion with the <code>schema</code> object, the example <em class=3D"rfc2119">=
MUST</em> follow the prescribed serialization strategy for the parameter.</=
p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"parameterContent"></span>content</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center">Map[<code>string</code>, <a href=3D"https:/=
/spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#media-type-object">Media Type Object</a>=
]</td>
<td>A map containing the representations for the parameter. The key is the =
media type and the value describes it. The map <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</=
em> only contain one entry.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</section><section id=3D"style-values"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=
=3D"x4-7-12-3-style-values"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.12.3 </bdi>Style Value=
s</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.h=
tml#style-values" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.12.3"></a></div>
<p>In order to support common ways of serializing simple parameters, a set =
of <code>style</code> values are defined.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th><code>style</code></th>
<th><a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#data-types"><code>=
type</code></a></th>
<th><code>in</code></th>
<th>Comments</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>matrix</td>
<td><code>primitive</code>, <code>array</code>, <code>object</code></td>
<td><code>path</code></td>
<td>Path-style parameters defined by [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-t=
ype=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc657=
0" title=3D"URI Template">RFC6570</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://datatracke=
r.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6570#section-3.2.7">Section 3.2.7</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>label</td>
<td><code>primitive</code>, <code>array</code>, <code>object</code></td>
<td><code>path</code></td>
<td>Label style parameters defined by [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-=
type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc65=
70" title=3D"URI Template">RFC6570</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://datatrack=
er.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6570#section-3.2.5">Section 3.2.5</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>form</td>
<td><code>primitive</code>, <code>array</code>, <code>object</code></td>
<td><code>query</code>, <code>cookie</code></td>
<td>Form style parameters defined by [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-t=
ype=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc657=
0" title=3D"URI Template">RFC6570</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://datatracke=
r.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6570#section-3.2.8">Section 3.2.8</a>. This option r=
eplaces <code>collectionFormat</code> with a <code>csv</code> (when <code>e=
xplode</code> is false) or <code>multi</code> (when <code>explode</code> is=
 true) value from OpenAPI 2.0.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>simple</td>
<td><code>array</code></td>
<td><code>path</code>, <code>header</code></td>
<td>Simple style parameters defined by [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link=
-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc6=
570" title=3D"URI Template">RFC6570</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://datatrac=
ker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6570#section-3.2.2">Section 3.2.2</a>.  This optio=
n replaces <code>collectionFormat</code> with a <code>csv</code> value from=
 OpenAPI 2.0.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>spaceDelimited</td>
<td><code>array</code></td>
<td><code>query</code></td>
<td>Space separated array values. This option replaces <code>collectionForm=
at</code> equal to <code>ssv</code> from OpenAPI 2.0.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>pipeDelimited</td>
<td><code>array</code></td>
<td><code>query</code></td>
<td>Pipe separated array values. This option replaces <code>collectionForma=
t</code> equal to <code>pipes</code> from OpenAPI 2.0.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>deepObject</td>
<td><code>object</code></td>
<td><code>query</code></td>
<td>Provides a simple way of rendering nested objects using form parameters=
.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</section><section id=3D"style-examples"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 =
id=3D"x4-7-12-4-style-examples"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.12.4 </bdi>Style E=
xamples</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3=
.0.3.html#style-examples" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.12.4"></a=
></div>
<p>Assume a parameter named <code>color</code> has one of the following val=
ues:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code>   string -&gt; "blue"
   array -&gt; ["blue","black","brown"]
   object -&gt; { "R": 100, "G": 200, "B": 150 }
</code></pre>
<p>The following table shows examples of rendering differences for each val=
ue.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th><a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#dataTypeFormat"><c=
ode>style</code></a></th>
<th><code>explode</code></th>
<th><code>empty</code></th>
<th><code>string</code></th>
<th><code>array</code></th>
<th><code>object</code></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>matrix</td>
<td>false</td>
<td>;color</td>
<td>;color=3Dblue</td>
<td>;color=3Dblue,black,brown</td>
<td>;color=3DR,100,G,200,B,150</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>matrix</td>
<td>true</td>
<td>;color</td>
<td>;color=3Dblue</td>
<td>;color=3Dblue;color=3Dblack;color=3Dbrown</td>
<td>;R=3D100;G=3D200;B=3D150</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>label</td>
<td>false</td>
<td>.</td>
<td>.blue</td>
<td>.blue.black.brown</td>
<td>.R.100.G.200.B.150</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>label</td>
<td>true</td>
<td>.</td>
<td>.blue</td>
<td>.blue.black.brown</td>
<td>.R=3D100.G=3D200.B=3D150</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>form</td>
<td>false</td>
<td>color=3D</td>
<td>color=3Dblue</td>
<td>color=3Dblue,black,brown</td>
<td>color=3DR,100,G,200,B,150</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>form</td>
<td>true</td>
<td>color=3D</td>
<td>color=3Dblue</td>
<td>color=3Dblue&amp;color=3Dblack&amp;color=3Dbrown</td>
<td>R=3D100&amp;G=3D200&amp;B=3D150</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>simple</td>
<td>false</td>
<td>n/a</td>
<td>blue</td>
<td>blue,black,brown</td>
<td>R,100,G,200,B,150</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>simple</td>
<td>true</td>
<td>n/a</td>
<td>blue</td>
<td>blue,black,brown</td>
<td>R=3D100,G=3D200,B=3D150</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>spaceDelimited</td>
<td>false</td>
<td>n/a</td>
<td>n/a</td>
<td>blue%20black%20brown</td>
<td>R%20100%20G%20200%20B%20150</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>pipeDelimited</td>
<td>false</td>
<td>n/a</td>
<td>n/a</td>
<td>blue|black|brown</td>
<td>R|100|G|200|B|150</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>deepObject</td>
<td>true</td>
<td>n/a</td>
<td>n/a</td>
<td>n/a</td>
<td>color[R]=3D100&amp;color[G]=3D200&amp;color[B]=3D150</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>This object <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be extended with <a href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#specification-extensions">Specific=
ation Extensions</a>.</p>
</section><section id=3D"parameter-object-examples"><div class=3D"header-wr=
apper"><h5 id=3D"x4-7-12-5-parameter-object-examples"><bdi class=3D"secno">=
4.7.12.5 </bdi>Parameter Object Examples</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D=
