<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"requestBodyDescription"></span>description</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>A brief description of the request body. This could contain examples of=
 use.  [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https:/=
/spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-commonmark" title=3D"CommonMark Spec=
">CommonMark</a></cite>] syntax <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be used for =
rich text representation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"requestBodyContent"></span>content</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center">Map[<code>string</code>, <a href=3D"https:/=
/spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#media-type-object">Media Type Object</a>=
]</td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. The content of th=
e request body. The key is a media type or media type range, see [<cite><a =
class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.or=
g/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc7231" title=3D"Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP/1=
.1): Semantics and Content">RFC7231</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://datatrac=
ker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7231#appendix-D">Appendix D</a>, and the value des=
cribes it.  For requests that match multiple keys, only the most specific k=
ey is applicable. e.g. text/plain overrides text/*</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"requestBodyRequired"></span>required</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>boolean</code></td>
<td>Determines if the request body is required in the request. Defaults to =
<code>false</code>.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
