<td style=3D"text-align:center">Map[ <code>string</code>, <a href=3D"https:=
//spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#example-object">Example Object</a> | <a=
 href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#reference-object">Refere=
nce Object</a>]</td>
<td>Examples of the media type.  Each example object <em class=3D"rfc2119">=
SHOULD</em>  match the media type and specified schema if present.  The <co=
de>examples</code> field is mutually exclusive of the <code>example</code> =
field.  Furthermore, if referencing a <code>schema</code> which contains an=
 example, the <code>examples</code> value <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> =
<em>override</em> the example provided by the schema.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"mediaTypeEncoding"></span>encoding</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center">Map[<code>string</code>, <a href=3D"https:/=
/spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#encoding-object">Encoding Object</a>]</t=
d>
<td>A map between a property name and its encoding information. The key, be=
ing the property name, <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> exist in the schema =
as a property. The encoding object <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> only ap=
ply to <code>requestBody</code> objects when the media type is <code>multip=
art</code> or <code>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</code>.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>This object <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be extended with <a href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#specification-extensions">Specific=
ation Extensions</a>.</p>
