</section><section id=3D"considerations-for-file-uploads"><div class=3D"hea=
der-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-7-14-3-considerations-for-file-uploads"><bdi clas=
s=3D"secno">4.7.14.3 </bdi>Considerations for File Uploads</h5><a class=3D"=
self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#considerations=
-for-file-uploads" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.14.3"></a></div>
<p>In contrast with the 2.0 specification, <code>file</code> input/output c=
ontent in OpenAPI is described with the same semantics as any other schema =
type. Specifically:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-comment=
"># content transferred with base64 encoding</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">string=
</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">base=
64</span>
</code></pre>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-comment=
"># content transferred in binary (octet-stream):</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">string=
</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">bina=
ry</span>
</code></pre>
<p>These examples apply to either input payloads of file uploads or respons=
e payloads.</p>
<p>A <code>requestBody</code> for submitting a file in a <code>POST</code> =
operation may look like the following example:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">r=
equestBody:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">content:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">application/octet-stream:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># a binary file of any type</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">=
string</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string=
">binary</span>
</code></pre>
<p>In addition, specific media types <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be spec=
ified:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-comment=
"># multiple, specific media types may be specified:</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-attr">requestBody:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">content:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># a binary file of type png or jpeg</spa=
n>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'image/jpeg':</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">=
string</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string=
">binary</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'image/png':</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">=
string</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string=
">binary</span>      =20
</code></pre>
<p>To upload multiple files, a <code>multipart</code> media type <em class=
=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be used:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">r=
equestBody:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">content:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">multipart/form-data:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># The property name 'file' will be u=
sed for all files.</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">file:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">array</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">items:</span>
              <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">string</span>
              <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-=
string">binary</span>

</code></pre>
</section><section id=3D"support-for-x-www-form-urlencoded-request-bodies">=
<div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-7-14-4-support-for-x-www-form-ur=
lencoded-request-bodies"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.14.4 </bdi>Support for x-=
www-form-urlencoded Request Bodies</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https=
://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#support-for-x-www-form-urlencoded-requ=
est-bodies" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.14.4"></a></div>
<p>To submit content using form url encoding via [<cite><a class=3D"bibref"=
 data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.htm=
l#bib-rfc1866" title=3D"Hypertext Markup Language - 2.0">RFC1866</a></cite>=
], the following
definition may be used:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">r=
equestBody:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">content:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">application/x-www-form-urlencoded:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">=
object</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">id:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">string</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">uuid</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">address:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># complex types are stringified to=
 support RFC 1866</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">object</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span> {}
</code></pre>
<p>In this example, the contents in the <code>requestBody</code> <em class=
=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be stringified per [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-l=
ink-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-r=
fc1866" title=3D"Hypertext Markup Language - 2.0">RFC1866</a></cite>] when =
passed to the server.  In addition, the <code>address</code> field complex =
object will be stringified.</p>
<p>When passing complex objects in the <code>application/x-www-form-urlenco=
ded</code> content type, the default serialization strategy of such propert=
ies is described in the <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.htm=
l#encoding-object"><code>Encoding Object</code></a>=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"ht=
tps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#encodingStyle"><code>style</code></=
a> property as <code>form</code>.</p>
</section><section id=3D"special-considerations-for-multipart-content"><div=
 class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-7-14-5-special-considerations-for-mu=
ltipart-content"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.14.5 </bdi>Special Considerations=
 for <code>multipart</code> Content</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"http=
s://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#special-considerations-for-multipart-=
content" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.14.5"></a></div>
<p>It is common to use <code>multipart/form-data</code> as a <code>Content-=
Type</code> when transferring request bodies to operations.  In contrast to=
 2.0, a <code>schema</code> is <em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em> to defin=
e the input parameters to the operation when using <code>multipart</code> c=
ontent.  This supports complex structures as well as supporting mechanisms =
for multiple file uploads.</p>
<p>When passing in <code>multipart</code> types, boundaries <em class=3D"rf=
c2119">MAY</em> be used to separate sections of the content being transferr=
ed =E2=80=94 thus, the following default <code>Content-Type</code>s are def=
ined for <code>multipart</code>:</p>
<ul>
<li>If the property is a primitive, or an array of primitive values, the de=
fault Content-Type is <code>text/plain</code></li>
<li>If the property is complex, or an array of complex values, the default =
Content-Type is <code>application/json</code></li>
<li>If the property is a <code>type: string</code> with <code>format: binar=
y</code> or <code>format: base64</code> (aka a file object), the default Co=
ntent-Type is <code>application/octet-stream</code></li>
</ul>
<p>Examples:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">r=
equestBody:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">content:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">multipart/form-data:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">=
object</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">id:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">string</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">uuid</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">address:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># default Content-Type for objects=
 is `application/json`</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">object</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span> {}
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">profileImage:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># default Content-Type for string/=
binary is `application/octet-stream`</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">string</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">binary</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">children:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># default Content-Type for arrays =
is based on the `inner` type (text/plain here)</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">array</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">items:</span>
              <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">string</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">addresses:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># default Content-Type for arrays =
is based on the `inner` type (object shown, so `application/json` in this e=
xample)</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">array</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">items:</span>
              <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">'#/components/schemas/Address'</span>
</code></pre>
<p>An <code>encoding</code> attribute is introduced to give you control ove=
r the serialization of parts of <code>multipart</code> request bodies.  Thi=
s attribute is <em>only</em> applicable to <code>multipart</code> and <code=
>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</code> request bodies.</p>
</section></section><section id=3D"encoding-object"><div class=3D"header-wr=
apper"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-15-encoding-object"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.15 </bdi=
>Encoding Object</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.o=
rg/oas/v3.0.3.html#encoding-object" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7=
.15"></a></div>
<p>A single encoding definition applied to a single schema property.</p>
<section id=3D"fixed-fields-12"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-=
7-15-1-fixed-fields"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.15.1 </bdi>Fixed Fields</h5><=
a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#fix=
ed-fields-12" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.15.1"></a></div>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"encodingContentType"></span>contentType</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>The Content-Type for encoding a specific property. Default value depend=
s on the property type: for <code>string</code> with <code>format</code> be=
ing <code>binary</code> =E2=80=93 <code>application/octet-stream</code>; fo=
r other primitive types =E2=80=93 <code>text/plain</code>; for <code>object=
</code> - <code>application/json</code>; for <code>array</code> =E2=80=93 t=
he default is defined based on the inner type. The value can be a specific =
media type (e.g. <code>application/json</code>), a wildcard media type (e.g=
. <code>image/*</code>), or a comma-separated list of the two types.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"encodingHeaders"></span>headers</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center">Map[<code>string</code>, <a href=3D"https:/=
/spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#header-object">Header Object</a> | <a hr=
ef=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#reference-object">Reference=
 Object</a>]</td>
<td>A map allowing additional information to be provided as headers, for ex=
ample <code>Content-Disposition</code>.  <code>Content-Type</code> is descr=
ibed separately and <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> be ignored in this sec=
tion. This property <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> be ignored if the requ=
est body media type is not a <code>multipart</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"encodingStyle"></span>style</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>Describes how a specific property value will be serialized depending on=
 its type.  See <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parame=
ter-object">Parameter Object</a> for details on the <a href=3D"https://spec=
.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameterStyle"><code>style</code></a> proper=
ty. The behavior follows the same values as <code>query</code> parameters, =
including default values. This property <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> be=
 ignored if the request body media type is not <code>application/x-www-form=
-urlencoded</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"encodingExplode"></span>explode</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>boolean</code></td>
<td>When this is true, property values of type <code>array</code> or <code>=
object</code> generate separate parameters for each value of the array, or =
key-value-pair of the map.  For other types of properties this property has=
 no effect. When <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#encod=
ingStyle"><code>style</code></a> is <code>form</code>, the default value is=
 <code>true</code>. For all other styles, the default value is <code>false<=
/code>. This property <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> be ignored if the re=
quest body media type is not <code>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</code>=
.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"encodingAllowReserved"></span>allowReserved</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>boolean</code></td>
<td>Determines whether the parameter value <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em=
> allow reserved characters, as defined by [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-=
link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-=
rfc3986" title=3D"Uniform Resource Identifier (URI): Generic Syntax">RFC398=
6</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc3986#sect=
ion-2.2">Section 2.2</a> <code>:/?#[]@!$&amp;'()*+,;=3D</code> to be includ=
ed without percent-encoding. The default value is <code>false</code>. This =
property <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> be ignored if the request body me=
dia type is not <code>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</code>.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>This object <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be extended with <a href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#specification-extensions">Specific=
ation Extensions</a>.</p>
</section><section id=3D"encoding-object-example"><div class=3D"header-wrap=
per"><h5 id=3D"x4-7-15-2-encoding-object-example"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.=
15.2 </bdi>Encoding Object Example</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https=
://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#encoding-object-example" aria-label=3D=
"Permalink for Section 4.7.15.2"></a></div>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">r=
equestBody:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">content:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">multipart/mixed:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">=
object</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">id:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># default is text/plain</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">string</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">uuid</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">address:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># default is application/json</spa=
n>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">object</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span> {}
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">historyMetadata:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># need to declare XML format!</spa=
n>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"hl=
js-string">metadata</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">in</span> <span clas=
s=3D"hljs-string">XML</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">format</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">object</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span> {}
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">profileImage:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># default is application/octet-str=
eam, need to declare an image type only!</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">string</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">binary</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">encoding:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">historyMetadata:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># require XML Content-Type in utf-8 =
encoding</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">contentType:</span> <span class=3D"hljs=
-string">application/xml;</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">charset=3Dutf-=
8</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">profileImage:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># only accept png/jpeg</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">contentType:</span> <span class=3D"hljs=
-string">image/png,</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">image/jpeg</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">headers:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">X-Rate-Limit-Limit:</span>
              <span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"=
hljs-string">The</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">number</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"hljs-string">of</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">allowed</span> <sp=
an class=3D"hljs-string">requests</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">in</sp=
an> <span class=3D"hljs-string">the</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">curr=
ent</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">period</span>
              <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
                <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-=
string">integer</span>
</code></pre>
</section></section><section id=3D"responses-object"><div class=3D"header-w=
rapper"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-16-responses-object"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.16 </b=
di>Responses Object</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapi=
s.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#responses-object" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section=
 4.7.16"></a></div>
<p>A container for the expected responses of an operation.
The container maps a HTTP response code to the expected response.</p>
<p>The documentation is not necessarily expected to cover all possible HTTP=
 response codes because they may not be known in advance.
However, documentation is expected to cover a successful operation response=
 and any known errors.</p>
<p>The <code>default</code> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be used as a def=
ault response object for all HTTP codes
that are not covered individually by the specification.</p>
<p>The <code>Responses Object</code> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> contai=
n at least one response code, and it
<em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> be the response for a successful operatio=
n call.</p>
<section id=3D"fixed-fields-13"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-=
7-16-1-fixed-fields"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.16.1 </bdi>Fixed Fields</h5><=
a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#fix=
ed-fields-13" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.16.1"></a></div>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"responsesDefault"></span>default</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3=
.0.3.html#response-object">Response Object</a> | <a href=3D"https://spec.op=
enapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#reference-object">Reference Object</a></td>
<td>The documentation of responses other than the ones declared for specifi=
c HTTP response codes. Use this field to cover undeclared responses. A <a h=
ref=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#reference-object">Referenc=
e Object</a> can link to a response that the <a href=3D"https://spec.openap=
is.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#componentsResponses">OpenAPI Object=E2=80=99s compon=
ents/responses</a> section defines.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</section><section id=3D"patterned-fields-0"><div class=3D"header-wrapper">=
<h5 id=3D"x4-7-16-2-patterned-fields"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.16.2 </bdi>P=
atterned Fields</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.or=
g/oas/v3.0.3.html#patterned-fields-0" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4=
.7.16.2"></a></div>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Pattern</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"responsesCode"></span><a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/=
oas/v3.0.3.html#http-status-codes">HTTP Status Code</a></td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3=
.0.3.html#response-object">Response Object</a> | <a href=3D"https://spec.op=
enapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#reference-object">Reference Object</a></td>
<td>Any <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#http-status-co=
des">HTTP status code</a> can be used as the property name, but only one pr=
operty per code, to describe the expected response for that HTTP status cod=
e.  A <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#reference-object=
">Reference Object</a> can link to a response that is defined in the <a hre=
f=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#componentsResponses">OpenAPI=
 Object=E2=80=99s components/responses</a> section. This field <em class=3D=
"rfc2119">MUST</em> be enclosed in quotation marks (for example, =E2=80=9C2=
00=E2=80=9D) for compatibility between JSON and YAML. To define a range of =
response codes, this field <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> contain the upper=
case wildcard character <code>X</code>. For example, <code>2XX</code> repre=
sents all response codes between <code>[200-299]</code>. Only the following=
 range definitions are allowed: <code>1XX</code>, <code>2XX</code>, <code>3=
XX</code>, <code>4XX</code>, and <code>5XX</code>. If a response is defined=
 using an explicit code, the explicit code definition takes precedence over=
 the range definition for that code.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>This object <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be extended with <a href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#specification-extensions">Specific=
ation Extensions</a>.</p>
</section><section id=3D"responses-object-example"><div class=3D"header-wra=
pper"><h5 id=3D"x4-7-16-3-responses-object-example"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.=
7.16.3 </bdi>Responses Object Example</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"ht=
tps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#responses-object-example" aria-labe=
l=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.16.3"></a></div>
<p>A 200 response for a successful operation and a default response for oth=
ers (implying an error):</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-punctua=
tion">{</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"200"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">:<=
