id=3D"x4-7-18-2-key-expression"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.18.2 </bdi>Key Exp=
ression</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3=
.0.3.html#key-expression" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.18.2"></a=
></div>
<p>The key that identifies the <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.=
0.3.html#path-item-object">Path Item Object</a> is a <a href=3D"https://spe=
c.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#runtime-expressions">runtime expression</a> =
that can be evaluated in the context of a runtime HTTP request/response to =
identify the URL to be used for the callback request.
A simple example might be <code>$request.body#/url</code>.
However, using a <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#runti=
me-expressions">runtime expression</a> the complete HTTP message can be acc=
essed.
This includes accessing any part of a body that a JSON Pointer [<cite><a cl=
ass=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/=
oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc6901" title=3D"JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) Poi=
nter">RFC6901</a></cite>] can reference.</p>
<p>For example, given the following HTTP request:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-keyword=
">POST</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">/subscribe/myevent?queryUrl=3Dhtt=
p://clientdomain.com/stillrunning</span> <span class=3D"hljs-meta">HTTP/1.1=
</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-attribute">Host</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">=
: </span>example.org
<span class=3D"hljs-attribute">Content-Type</span><span class=3D"hljs-punct=
uation">: </span>application/json
<span class=3D"hljs-attribute">Content-Length</span><span class=3D"hljs-pun=
ctuation">: </span>187

<span class=3D"language-uri">{
  "failedUrl" : "http://<span class=3D"hljs-attr">clientdomain.com</span>/<=
span class=3D"hljs-attr">failed",</span>
  "successUrls" : [
    "http://<span class=3D"hljs-attr">clientdomain.com</span>/<span class=
=3D"hljs-attr">fast",</span>
    "http://<span class=3D"hljs-attr">clientdomain.com</span>/<span class=
=3D"hljs-attr">medium",</span>
    "http://<span class=3D"hljs-attr">clientdomain.com</span>/<span class=
=3D"hljs-attr">slow"</span>
  ]
}

201 Created
Location: http://<span class=3D"hljs-attr">example.org</span>/<span class=
=3D"hljs-attr">subscription</span>/<span class=3D"hljs-attr">1</span>
</span></code></pre>
<p>The following examples show how the various expressions evaluate, assumi=
ng the callback operation has a path parameter named <code>eventType</code>=
 and a query parameter named <code>queryUrl</code>.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Expression</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:left">Value</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>$url</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><a href=3D"http://example.org/subscribe/myeve=
nt?queryUrl=3Dhttp://clientdomain.com/stillrunning">http://example.org/subs=
cribe/myevent?queryUrl=3Dhttp://clientdomain.com/stillrunning</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>$method</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left">POST</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>$request.path.eventType</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left">myevent</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>$request.query.queryUrl</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><a href=3D"http://clientdomain.com/stillrunni=
ng">http://clientdomain.com/stillrunning</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>$request.header.content-Type</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left">application/json</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>$request.body#/failedUrl</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><a href=3D"http://clientdomain.com/failed">ht=
tp://clientdomain.com/failed</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>$request.body#/successUrls/2</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><a href=3D"http://clientdomain.com/medium">ht=
tp://clientdomain.com/medium</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>$response.header.Location</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><a href=3D"http://example.org/subscription/1"=
>http://example.org/subscription/1</a></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</section><section id=3D"callback-object-examples"><div class=3D"header-wra=
pper"><h5 id=3D"x4-7-18-3-callback-object-examples"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.=
7.18.3 </bdi>Callback Object Examples</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"ht=
tps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#callback-object-examples" aria-labe=
l=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.18.3"></a></div>
<p>The following example uses the user provided <code>queryUrl</code> query=
 string parameter to define the callback URL.  This is an example of how to=
 use a callback object to describe a WebHook callback that goes with the su=
bscription operation to enable registering for the WebHook.</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">m=
yCallback:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-string">'{$request.query.queryUrl}'</span><span class=
=3D"hljs-string">:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">post:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">requestBody:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-s=
tring">Callback</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">payload</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">content:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'application/json':</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
              <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-=
string">'#/components/schemas/SomePayload'</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">responses:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'200':</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"hljs=
-string">callback</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">successfully</span> <s=
pan class=3D"hljs-string">processed</span>
</code></pre>
<p>The following example shows a callback where the server is hard-coded, b=
ut the query string parameters are populated from the <code>id</code> and <=
code>email</code> property in the request body.</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">t=
ransactionCallback:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-string">'http://notificationServer.com?transactionId=
=3D{$request.body#/id}&amp;email=3D{$request.body#/email}'</span><span clas=
s=3D"hljs-string">:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">post:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">requestBody:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-s=
tring">Callback</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">payload</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">content:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'application/json':</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
              <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-=
string">'#/components/schemas/SomePayload'</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">responses:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'200':</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"hljs=
-string">callback</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">successfully</span> <s=
pan class=3D"hljs-string">processed</span>
</code></pre>
</section></section><section id=3D"example-object"><div class=3D"header-wra=
pper"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-19-example-object"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.19 </bdi>E=
xample Object</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/=
oas/v3.0.3.html#example-object" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.19"=
></a></div>
<section id=3D"fixed-fields-15"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-=
7-19-1-fixed-fields"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.19.1 </bdi>Fixed Fields</h5><=
a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#fix=
ed-fields-15" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.19.1"></a></div>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"exampleSummary"></span>summary</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>Short description for the example.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"exampleDescription"></span>description</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>Long description for the example. [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-=
type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-commo=
nmark" title=3D"CommonMark Spec">CommonMark</a></cite>] syntax <em class=3D=
"rfc2119">MAY</em> be used for rich text representation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"exampleValue"></span>value</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center">Any</td>
<td>Embedded literal example. The <code>value</code> field and <code>extern=
alValue</code> field are mutually exclusive. To represent examples of media=
 types that cannot naturally represented in JSON or YAML, use a string valu=
e to contain the example, escaping where necessary.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"exampleExternalValue"></span>externalValue</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>A URL that points to the literal example. This provides the capability =
to reference examples that cannot easily be included in JSON or YAML docume=
nts.  The <code>value</code> field and <code>externalValue</code> field are=
 mutually exclusive.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>This object <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be extended with <a href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#specification-extensions">Specific=
ation Extensions</a>.</p>
<p>In all cases, the example value is expected to be compatible with the ty=
pe schema
of its associated value.  Tooling implementations <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY=
</em> choose to
validate compatibility automatically, and reject the example value(s) if in=
compatible.</p>
</section><section id=3D"example-object-examples"><div class=3D"header-wrap=
per"><h5 id=3D"x4-7-19-2-example-object-examples"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.=
19.2 </bdi>Example Object Examples</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https=
://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#example-object-examples" aria-label=3D=
"Permalink for Section 4.7.19.2"></a></div>
<p>In a request body:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">r=
equestBody:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">content:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'application/json':</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string=
">'#/components/schemas/Address'</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">examples:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">foo:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">summary:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-str=
ing">A</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">foo</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">example</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">value:</span> {<span class=3D"hljs-attr=
">"foo":</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"bar"</span>}
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">bar:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">summary:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-str=
ing">A</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">bar</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">example</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">value:</span> {<span class=3D"hljs-attr=
">"bar":</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"baz"</span>}
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'application/xml':</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">examples:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">xmlExample:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">summary:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-str=
ing">This</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">is</span> <span class=3D"hljs-=
string">an</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">example</span> <span class=3D=
"hljs-string">in</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">XML</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">externalValue:</span> <span class=3D"hl=
js-string">'http://example.org/examples/address-example.xml'</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'text/plain':</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">examples:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">textExample:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">summary:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-str=
ing">This</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">is</span> <span class=3D"hljs-=
string">a</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">text</span> <span class=3D"hlj=
s-string">example</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">externalValue:</span> <span class=3D"hl=
js-string">'http://foo.bar/examples/address-example.txt'</span>
</code></pre>
<p>In a parameter:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">p=
arameters:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-attr">name:</spa=
n> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'zipCode'</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">in:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'query=
'</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'s=
tring'</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">=
'zip-code'</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">examples:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">zip-example:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string=
">'#/components/examples/zip-example'</span>
</code></pre>
<p>In a response:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">r=
esponses:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'200':</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-strin=
g">your</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">car</span> <span class=3D"hljs-s=
tring">appointment</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">has</span> <span clas=
s=3D"hljs-string">been</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">booked</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">content:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">application/json:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">'#/components/schemas/SuccessResponse'</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">examples:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">confirmation-success:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">'#/components/examples/confirmation-success'</span>
</code></pre>
</section></section><section id=3D"link-object"><div class=3D"header-wrappe=
r"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-20-link-object"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.20 </bdi>Link Ob=
ject</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.=
3.html#link-object" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.20"></a></div>
<p>The <code>Link object</code> represents a possible design-time link for =
a response.
The presence of a link does not guarantee the caller=E2=80=99s ability to s=
uccessfully invoke it, rather it provides a known relationship and traversa=
l mechanism between responses and other operations.</p>
<p>Unlike <em>dynamic</em> links (i.e. links provided <strong>in</strong> t=
he response payload), the OAS linking mechanism does not require link infor=
mation in the runtime response.</p>
<p>For computing links, and providing instructions to execute them, a <a hr=
ef=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#runtime-expressions">runtim=
e expression</a> is used for accessing values in an operation and using the=
m as parameters while invoking the linked operation.</p>
<section id=3D"fixed-fields-16"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-=
7-20-1-fixed-fields"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.20.1 </bdi>Fixed Fields</h5><=
a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#fix=
ed-fields-16" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.20.1"></a></div>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"linkOperationRef"></span>operationRef</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>A relative or absolute URI reference to an OAS operation. This field is=
 mutually exclusive of the <code>operationId</code> field, and <em class=3D=
"rfc2119">MUST</em> point to an <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3=
.0.3.html#operation-object">Operation Object</a>. Relative <code>operationR=
ef</code> values <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be used to locate an existi=
ng <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#operation-object">O=
peration Object</a> in the OpenAPI definition.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"linkOperationId"></span>operationId</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>The name of an <em>existing</em>, resolvable OAS operation, as defined =
with a unique <code>operationId</code>.  This field is mutually exclusive o=
f the <code>operationRef</code> field.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"linkParameters"></span>parameters</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center">Map[<code>string</code>, Any | <a href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#runtime-expressions">{expression}<=
/a>]</td>
<td>A map representing parameters to pass to an operation as specified with=
 <code>operationId</code> or identified via <code>operationRef</code>. The =
key is the parameter name to be used, whereas the value can be a constant o=
r an expression to be evaluated and passed to the linked operation.  The pa=
rameter name can be qualified using the <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.or=
g/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameterIn">parameter location</a> <code>[{in}.]{name}</=
code> for operations that use the same parameter name in different location=
s (e.g. <a href=3D"http://path.id/">path.id</a>).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"linkRequestBody"></span>requestBody</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center">Any | <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/=
oas/v3.0.3.html#runtime-expressions">{expression}</a></td>
<td>A literal value or <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html=
#runtime-expressions">{expression}</a> to use as a request body when callin=
g the target operation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"linkDescription"></span>description</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>A description of the link. [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D=
"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-commonmark" =
title=3D"CommonMark Spec">CommonMark</a></cite>] syntax <em class=3D"rfc211=
9">MAY</em> be used for rich text representation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"linkServer"></span>server</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3=
.0.3.html#server-object">Server Object</a></td>
<td>A server object to be used by the target operation.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>This object <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be extended with <a href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#specification-extensions">Specific=
ation Extensions</a>.</p>
<p>A linked operation <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be identified using e=
ither an <code>operationRef</code> or <code>operationId</code>.
In the case of an <code>operationId</code>, it <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</=
em> be unique and resolved in the scope of the OAS document.
Because of the potential for name clashes, the <code>operationRef</code> sy=
ntax is preferred
for specifications with external references.</p>
</section><section id=3D"examples"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"=
x4-7-20-2-examples"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.20.2 </bdi>Examples</h5><a cla=
ss=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#examples=
" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.20.2"></a></div>
<p>Computing a link from a request operation where the <code>$request.path.=
id</code> is used to pass a request parameter to the linked operation.</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">p=
aths:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-string">/users/{id}:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">parameters:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-attr">name:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">id</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">in:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">path=
</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">required:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-litera=
l">true</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-str=
ing">the</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">user</span> <span class=3D"hljs=
-string">identifier,</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">as</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"hljs-string">userId</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">=
string</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">get:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">responses:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'200':</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"hljs=
-string">the</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">user</span> <span class=3D"=
hljs-string">being</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">returned</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">content:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">application/json:</span>
              <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
                <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-=
string">object</span>
                <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span>
                  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">uuid:</span> <span class=3D"hlj=
s-comment"># the unique user id</span>
                    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"h=
ljs-string">string</span>
                    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">format:</span> <span class=3D=
"hljs-string">uuid</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">links:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">address:</span>
              <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># the target link operationId</s=
pan>
              <span class=3D"hljs-attr">operationId:</span> <span class=3D"=
hljs-string">getUserAddress</span>
              <span class=3D"hljs-attr">parameters:</span>
                <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># get the `id` field from the =
request path parameter named `id`</span>
                <span class=3D"hljs-attr">userId:</span> <span class=3D"hlj=
s-string">$request.path.id</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># the path item of the linked operation</spa=
n>
  <span class=3D"hljs-string">/users/{userid}/address:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">parameters:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-attr">name:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">userid</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">in:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">path=
</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">required:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-litera=
l">true</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-str=
ing">the</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">user</span> <span class=3D"hljs=
-string">identifier,</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">as</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"hljs-string">userId</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">=
string</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># linked operation</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">get:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">operationId:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-str=
ing">getUserAddress</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">responses:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">'200':</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"hljs=
-string">the</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">user's</span> <span class=
=3D"hljs-string">address</span>
</code></pre>
<p>When a runtime expression fails to evaluate, no parameter value is passe=
d to the target operation.</p>
<p>Values from the response body can be used to drive a linked operation.</=
p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">l=
inks:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">address:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">operationId:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-strin=
g">getUserAddressByUUID</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">parameters:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># get the `uuid` field from the `uuid` f=
ield in the response body</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">userUuid:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string=
">$response.body#/uuid</span>
</code></pre>
<p>Clients follow all links at their discretion.
Neither permissions, nor the capability to make a successful call to that l=
ink, is guaranteed
solely by the existence of a relationship.</p>
</section><section id=3D"operationref-examples"><div class=3D"header-wrappe=
r"><h5 id=3D"x4-7-20-3-operationref-examples"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.20.3=
 </bdi>OperationRef Examples</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spe=
c.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#operationref-examples" aria-label=3D"Permali=
nk for Section 4.7.20.3"></a></div>
<p>As references to <code>operationId</code> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em>=
 NOT be possible (the <code>operationId</code> is an optional
field in an <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#operation-=
object">Operation Object</a>), references <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> al=
so be made through a relative <code>operationRef</code>:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">l=
inks:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">UserRepositories:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># returns array of '#/components/schemas/r=
epository'</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">operationRef:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">'#/paths/~12.0~1repositories~1{username}/get'</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">parameters:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">username:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string=
">$response.body#/username</span>
</code></pre>
<p>or an absolute <code>operationRef</code>:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">l=
inks:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">UserRepositories:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># returns array of '#/components/schemas/r=
epository'</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">operationRef:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">'https://na2.gigantic-server.com/#/paths/~12.0~1repositories~1{username=
}/get'</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">parameters:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">username:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string=
">$response.body#/username</span>
</code></pre>
<p>Note that in the use of <code>operationRef</code>, the <em>escaped forwa=
rd-slash</em> is necessary when
using JSON references.</p>
</section><section id=3D"runtime-expressions"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"=
><h5 id=3D"x4-7-20-4-runtime-expressions"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.20.4 </b=
di>Runtime Expressions</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.open=
apis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#runtime-expressions" aria-label=3D"Permalink for S=
ection 4.7.20.4"></a></div>
<p>Runtime expressions allow defining values based on information that will=
 only be available within the HTTP message in an actual API call.
This mechanism is used by <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.h=
tml#link-object">Link Objects</a> and <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/=
oas/v3.0.3.html#callback-object">Callback Objects</a>.</p>
<p>The runtime expression is defined by the following [<cite><a class=3D"bi=
bref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.=
3.html#bib-abnf" title=3D"Augmented BNF for Syntax Specifications: ABNF">AB=
NF</a></cite>] syntax</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code>      expression <span clas=
s=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> ( <span class=3D"hljs-string">"$url"</span> =
/ <span class=3D"hljs-string">"$method"</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-string=
">"$statusCode"</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-string">"$request."</span> sou=
rce / <span class=3D"hljs-string">"$response."</span> source )
      source <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> ( header-reference / =
query-reference / path-reference / body-reference )
      header-reference <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> <span class=
=3D"hljs-string">"header."</span> token
      query-reference <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> <span class=
=3D"hljs-string">"query."</span> name=20
      path-reference <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> <span class=
=3D"hljs-string">"path."</span> name
      body-reference <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> <span class=
=3D"hljs-string">"body"</span> [<span class=3D"hljs-string">"#"</span> json=
-pointer ]
      json-pointer    <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> *( <span cla=
ss=3D"hljs-string">"/"</span> reference-token )
      reference-token <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> *( unescaped=
 / escaped )
      unescaped       <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> <span class=
=3D"hljs-symbol">%x00-2E</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-symbol">%x30-7D</span=
> / <span class=3D"hljs-symbol">%x7F-10FFFF</span>
         <span class=3D"hljs-comment">; %x2F ('/') and %x7E ('~') are exclu=
ded from 'unescaped'</span>
      escaped         <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> <span class=
=3D"hljs-string">"~"</span> ( <span class=3D"hljs-string">"0"</span> / <spa=
n class=3D"hljs-string">"1"</span> )
        <span class=3D"hljs-comment">; representing '~' and '/', respective=
ly</span>
      name <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> *( <span class=3D"hljs-=
keyword">CHAR</span> )
      token <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> <span class=3D"hljs-nu=
mber">1</span>*tchar
      tchar <span class=3D"hljs-operator">=3D</span> <span class=3D"hljs-st=
ring">"!"</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-string">"#"</span> / <span class=3D"=
hljs-string">"$"</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-string">"%"</span> / <span cl=
ass=3D"hljs-string">"&amp;"</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-string">"'"</span>=
 / <span class=3D"hljs-string">"*"</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-string">"+"=
</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-string">"-"</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">"."</span> /
        <span class=3D"hljs-string">"^"</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-string=
">"_"</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-string">"`"</span> / <span class=3D"hljs=
-string">"|"</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-string">"~"</span> / <span class=
=3D"hljs-keyword">DIGIT</span> / <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">ALPHA</span>
</code></pre>
<p>Here, <code>json-pointer</code> is taken from [<cite><a class=3D"bibref"=
 data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.htm=
l#bib-rfc6901" title=3D"JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) Pointer">RFC6901<=
/a></cite>], <code>char</code> from [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-ty=
pe=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc7159=
" title=3D"The JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) Data Interchange Format">R=
FC7159</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7159=
#section-7">Section 7</a> and <code>token</code> from [<cite><a class=3D"bi=
bref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.=
3.html#bib-rfc7230" title=3D"Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP/1.1): Messag=
e Syntax and Routing">RFC7230</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://datatracker.ie=
tf.org/doc/html/rfc7230#section-3.2.6">Section 3.2.6</a>.</p>
<p>The <code>name</code> identifier is case-sensitive, whereas <code>token<=
/code> is not.</p>
<p>The table below provides examples of runtime expressions and examples of=
 their use in a value:</p>
</section><section id=3D"examples-0"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=
=3D"x4-7-20-5-examples"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.20.5 </bdi>Examples</h5><a=
 class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#exam=
ples-0" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.20.5"></a></div>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Source Location</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:left">example expression</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:left">notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>HTTP Method</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><code>$method</code></td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left">The allowable values for the <code>$method</c=
ode> will be those for the HTTP operation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Requested media type</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><code>$request.header.accept</code></td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Request parameter</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><code>$request.path.id</code></td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left">Request parameters <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST=
</em> be declared in the <code>parameters</code> section of the parent oper=
ation or they cannot be evaluated. This includes request headers.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Request body property</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><code>$request.body#/user/uuid</code></td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left">In operations which accept payloads, referenc=
es may be made to portions of the <code>requestBody</code> or the entire bo=
dy.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Request URL</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><code>$url</code></td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Response value</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><code>$response.body#/status</code></td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left">In operations which return payloads, referenc=
es may be made to portions of the response body or the entire body.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Response header</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left"><code>$response.header.Server</code></td>
<td style=3D"text-align:left">Single header values only are available</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>Runtime expressions preserve the type of the referenced value.
Expressions can be embedded into string values by surrounding the expressio=
n with <code>{}</code> curly braces.</p>
</section></section><section id=3D"header-object"><div class=3D"header-wrap=
per"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-21-header-object"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.21 </bdi>Hea=
der Object</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas=
/v3.0.3.html#header-object" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.21"></a=
></div>
<p>The Header Object follows the structure of the <a href=3D"https://spec.o=
penapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameter-object">Parameter Object</a> with the=
 following changes:</p>
<ol>
<li><code>name</code> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST NOT</em> be specified, it =
is given in the corresponding <code>headers</code> map.</li>
<li><code>in</code> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST NOT</em> be specified, it is=
 implicitly in <code>header</code>.</li>
<li>All traits that are affected by the location <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST=
</em> be applicable to a location of <code>header</code> (for example, <a h=
ref=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#parameterStyle"><code>styl=
e</code></a>).</li>
</ol>
<section id=3D"header-object-example"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=
=3D"x4-7-21-1-header-object-example"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.21.1 </bdi>He=
ader Object Example</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapi=
s.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#header-object-example" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Se=
ction 4.7.21.1"></a></div>
<p>A simple header of type <code>integer</code>:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-punctua=
tion">{</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"description"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctua=
tion">:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"The number of allowed requests =
in the current period"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">,</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"schema"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation"=
>:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">{</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"type"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation"=
>:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"integer"</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">}</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">d=
escription:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">The</span> <span class=3D"hl=
js-string">number</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">of</span> <span class=
=3D"hljs-string">allowed</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">requests</span>=
 <span class=3D"hljs-string">in</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">the</spa=
n> <span class=3D"hljs-string">current</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">p=
eriod</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-attr">schema:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">intege=
r</span>
</code></pre>
</section></section><section id=3D"tag-object"><div class=3D"header-wrapper=
"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-22-tag-object"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.22 </bdi>Tag Objec=
t</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.h=
tml#tag-object" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.22"></a></div>
<p>Adds metadata to a single tag that is used by the <a href=3D"https://spe=
c.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#operation-object">Operation Object</a>.
It is not mandatory to have a Tag Object per tag defined in the Operation O=
bject instances.</p>
<section id=3D"fixed-fields-17"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-=
7-22-1-fixed-fields"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.22.1 </bdi>Fixed Fields</h5><=
a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#fix=
ed-fields-17" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.22.1"></a></div>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"tagName"></span>name</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. The name of the t=
ag.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"tagDescription"></span>description</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>A short description for the tag. [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-t=
ype=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-common=
mark" title=3D"CommonMark Spec">CommonMark</a></cite>] syntax <em class=3D"=
rfc2119">MAY</em> be used for rich text representation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"tagExternalDocs"></span>externalDocs</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3=
.0.3.html#external-documentation-object">External Documentation Object</a><=
/td>
<td>Additional external documentation for this tag.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>This object <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be extended with <a href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#specification-extensions">Specific=
ation Extensions</a>.</p>
</section><section id=3D"tag-object-example"><div class=3D"header-wrapper">=
<h5 id=3D"x4-7-22-2-tag-object-example"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.22.2 </bdi=
>Tag Object Example</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapi=
s.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#tag-object-example" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Secti=
on 4.7.22.2"></a></div>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-punctua=
tion">{</span>
	<span class=3D"hljs-attr">"name"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">:<=
/span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"pet"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuat=
ion">,</span>
	<span class=3D"hljs-attr">"description"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuat=
ion">:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"Pets operations"</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">n=
ame:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">pet</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-attr">description:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">P=
ets</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">operations</span>
</code></pre>
</section></section><section id=3D"reference-object"><div class=3D"header-w=
rapper"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-23-reference-object"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.23 </b=
di>Reference Object</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapi=
s.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#reference-object" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section=
 4.7.23"></a></div>
<p>A simple object to allow referencing other components in the specificati=
on, internally and externally.</p>
<p>The Reference Object is defined by <cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-t=
ype=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-json-r=
eference" title=3D"JSON Reference">JSON Reference</a></cite> and follows th=
e same structure, behavior and rules.</p>
<p>For this specification, reference resolution is accomplished as defined =
by the JSON Reference specification and not by the JSON Schema specificatio=
n.</p>
<section id=3D"fixed-fields-18"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-=
7-23-1-fixed-fields"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.23.1 </bdi>Fixed Fields</h5><=
a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#fix=
ed-fields-18" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.23.1"></a></div>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"referenceRef"></span>$ref</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. The reference str=
ing.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>This object cannot be extended with additional properties and any proper=
ties added <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHALL</em> be ignored.</p>
