</section></section></section><section id=3D"discriminator-object"><div cla=
ss=3D"header-wrapper"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-25-discriminator-object"><bdi class=3D=
"secno">4.7.25 </bdi>Discriminator Object</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=
=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#discriminator-object" aria-la=
bel=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.25"></a></div>
<p>When request bodies or response payloads may be one of a number of diffe=
rent schemas, a <code>discriminator</code> object can be used to aid in ser=
ialization, deserialization, and validation.  The discriminator is a specif=
ic object in a schema which is used to inform the consumer of the specifica=
tion of an alternative schema based on the value associated with it.</p>
<p>When using the discriminator, <em>inline</em> schemas will not be consid=
ered.</p>
<section id=3D"fixed-fields-20"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-=
7-25-1-fixed-fields"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.25.1 </bdi>Fixed Fields</h5><=
a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#fix=
ed-fields-20" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.25.1"></a></div>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"propertyName"></span>propertyName</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. The name of the p=
roperty in the payload that will hold the discriminator value.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"discriminatorMapping"></span> mapping</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center">Map[<code>string</code>, <code>string</code=
>]</td>
<td>An object to hold mappings between payload values and schema names or r=
eferences.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>The discriminator object is legal only when using one of the composite k=
eywords <code>oneOf</code>, <code>anyOf</code>, <code>allOf</code>.</p>
<p>In OAS 3.0, a response payload <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be describ=
ed to be exactly one of any number of types:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">M=
yResponseType:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">oneOf:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Cat'</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Dog'</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Lizard'</span>
</code></pre>
<p>which means the payload <em><em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em></em>, by val=
idation, match exactly one of the schemas described by <code>Cat</code>, <c=
ode>Dog</code>, or <code>Lizard</code>.  In this case, a discriminator <em =
class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> act as a =E2=80=9Chint=E2=80=9D to shortcut vali=
dation and selection of the matching schema which may be a costly operation=
, depending on the complexity of the schema. We can then describe exactly w=
hich field tells us which schema to use:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">M=
yResponseType:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">oneOf:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Cat'</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Dog'</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Lizard'</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">discriminator:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">propertyName:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">petType</span>
</code></pre>
<p>The expectation now is that a property with name <code>petType</code> <e=
m><em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em></em> be present in the response payload, =
and the value will correspond to the name of a schema defined in the OAS do=
cument.  Thus the response payload:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-punctua=
tion">{</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"id"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">:</=
span> <span class=3D"hljs-number">12345</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuati=
on">,</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"petType"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation=
">:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"Cat"</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre>
<p>Will indicate that the <code>Cat</code> schema be used in conjunction wi=
th this payload.</p>
<p>In scenarios where the value of the discriminator field does not match t=
he schema name or implicit mapping is not possible, an optional <code>mappi=
ng</code> definition <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be used:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">M=
yResponseType:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">oneOf:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Cat'</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Dog'</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Lizard'</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref:</s=
pan> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'https://gigantic-server.com/schemas/Monst=
er/schema.json'</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">discriminator:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">propertyName:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">petType</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">mapping:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">dog:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/=
components/schemas/Dog'</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">monster:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string"=
>'https://gigantic-server.com/schemas/Monster/schema.json'</span>
</code></pre>
<p>Here the discriminator <em>value</em> of <code>dog</code> will map to th=
e schema <code>#/components/schemas/Dog</code>, rather than the default (im=
plicit) value of <code>Dog</code>.  If the discriminator <em>value</em> doe=
s not match an implicit or explicit mapping, no schema can be determined an=
d validation <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> fail. Mapping keys <em class=
=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be string values, but tooling <em class=3D"rfc2119">=
MAY</em> convert response values to strings for comparison.</p>
<p>When used in conjunction with the <code>anyOf</code> construct, the use =
of the discriminator can avoid ambiguity where multiple schemas may satisfy=
 a single payload.</p>
<p>In both the <code>oneOf</code> and <code>anyOf</code> use cases, all pos=
sible schemas <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be listed explicitly.  To avo=
id redundancy, the discriminator <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be added to=
 a parent schema definition, and all schemas comprising the parent schema i=
n an <code>allOf</code> construct may be used as an alternate schema.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-attr">c=
omponents:</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">schemas:</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">Pet:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">ob=
ject</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">required:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">petT=
ype</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">petType:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string=
">string</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">discriminator:</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">propertyName:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-=
string">petType</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">mapping:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">dog:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string"=
>Dog</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">Cat:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">allOf:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref=
:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Pet'</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:<=
/span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">object</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># all other properties specific to a `=
Cat`</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">name:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">string</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">Dog:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">allOf:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref=
:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Pet'</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:<=
/span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">object</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># all other properties specific to a `=
Dog`</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">bark:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">string</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-attr">Lizard:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-attr">allOf:</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">$ref=
:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">'#/components/schemas/Pet'</span>
      <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:<=
/span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">object</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># all other properties specific to a `=
Lizard`</span>
        <span class=3D"hljs-attr">properties:</span>
          <span class=3D"hljs-attr">lovesRocks:</span>
            <span class=3D"hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-stri=
ng">boolean</span>
</code></pre>
<p>a payload like this:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-punctua=
tion">{</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"petType"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation=
">:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"Cat"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punc=
tuation">,</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"name"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">:=
</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"misty"</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre>
<p>will indicate that the <code>Cat</code> schema be used.  Likewise this s=
chema:</p>
<pre class=3D"nohighlight" tabindex=3D"0"><code><span class=3D"hljs-punctua=
tion">{</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"petType"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation=
">:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"dog"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punc=
tuation">,</span>
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">"bark"</span><span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">:=
</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">"soft"</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre>
<p>will map to <code>Dog</code> because of the definition in the <code>mapp=
ings</code> element.</p>
</section></section><section id=3D"xml-object"><div class=3D"header-wrapper=
"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-26-xml-object"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.26 </bdi>XML Objec=
t</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.h=
tml#xml-object" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.26"></a></div>
<p>A metadata object that allows for more fine-tuned XML model definitions.=
</p>
<p>When using arrays, XML element names are <em>not</em> inferred (for sing=
ular/plural forms) and the <code>name</code> property <em class=3D"rfc2119"=
>SHOULD</em> be used to add that information.
See examples for expected behavior.</p>
<section id=3D"fixed-fields-21"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-=
7-26-1-fixed-fields"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.26.1 </bdi>Fixed Fields</h5><=
a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#fix=
ed-fields-21" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.26.1"></a></div>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"xmlName"></span>name</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>Replaces the name of the element/attribute used for the described schem=
a property. When defined within <code>items</code>, it will affect the name=
 of the individual XML elements within the list. When defined alongside <co=
de>type</code> being <code>array</code> (outside the <code>items</code>), i=
t will affect the wrapping element and only if <code>wrapped</code> is <cod=
e>true</code>. If <code>wrapped</code> is <code>false</code>, it will be ig=
nored.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"xmlNamespace"></span>namespace</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>The URI of the namespace definition. Value <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</=
em> be in the form of an absolute URI.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"xmlPrefix"></span>prefix</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>The prefix to be used for the <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/=
v3.0.3.html#xmlName">name</a>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"xmlAttribute"></span>attribute</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>boolean</code></td>
<td>Declares whether the property definition translates to an attribute ins=
tead of an element. Default value is <code>false</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"xmlWrapped"></span>wrapped</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>boolean</code></td>
<td><em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be used only for an array definition. Si=
gnifies whether the array is wrapped (for example, <code>&lt;books&gt;&lt;b=
ook/&gt;&lt;book/&gt;&lt;/books&gt;</code>) or unwrapped (<code>&lt;book/&g=
t;&lt;book/&gt;</code>). Default value is <code>false</code>. The definitio=
n takes effect only when defined alongside <code>type</code> being <code>ar=
ray</code> (outside the <code>items</code>).</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>This object <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be extended with <a href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#specification-extensions">Specific=
ation Extensions</a>.</p>
</section><section id=3D"xml-object-examples"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"=
><h5 id=3D"x4-7-26-2-xml-object-examples"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.26.2 </b=
di>XML Object Examples</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.open=
apis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#xml-object-examples" aria-label=3D"Permalink for S=
ection 4.7.26.2"></a></div>
<p>The examples of the XML object definitions are included inside a propert=
y definition of a <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#sche=
ma-object">Schema Object</a> with a sample of the XML representation of it.=
</p>
<section id=3D"no-xml-element"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h6 id=3D"x4-7=
-26-2-1-no-xml-element"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.26.2.1 </bdi>No XML Elemen=
t</h6><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.h=
tml#no-xml-element" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.26.2.1"></a></d=
iv>
<p>Basic string property:</p>
