lass=3D"header-wrapper"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-27-security-scheme-object"><bdi clas=
s=3D"secno">4.7.27 </bdi>Security Scheme Object</h4><a class=3D"self-link" =
href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#security-scheme-object" a=
ria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.27"></a></div>
<p>Defines a security scheme that can be used by the operations.
Supported schemes are HTTP authentication, an API key (either as a header, =
a cookie parameter or as a query parameter), OAuth2=E2=80=99s common flows =
(implicit, password, client credentials and authorization code) as defined =
in [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spe=
c.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc6749" title=3D"The OAuth 2.0 Authoriz=
ation Framework">RFC6749</a></cite>], and <a href=3D"https://tools.ietf.org=
/html/draft-ietf-oauth-discovery-06">OpenID Connect Discovery</a>.</p>
<section id=3D"fixed-fields-22"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x4-=
7-27-1-fixed-fields"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.7.27.1 </bdi>Fixed Fields</h5><=
a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#fix=
ed-fields-22" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.27.1"></a></div>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th style=3D"text-align:center">Type</th>
<th>Applies To</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"securitySchemeType"></span>type</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>Any</td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. The type of the s=
ecurity scheme. Valid values are <code>"apiKey"</code>, <code>"http"</code>=
, <code>"oauth2"</code>, <code>"openIdConnect"</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"securitySchemeDescription"></span>description</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td>Any</td>
<td>A short description for security scheme. [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" dat=
a-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bi=
b-commonmark" title=3D"CommonMark Spec">CommonMark</a></cite>] syntax <em c=
lass=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be used for rich text representation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"securitySchemeName"></span>name</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td><code>apiKey</code></td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. The name of the h=
eader, query or cookie parameter to be used.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"securitySchemeIn"></span>in</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td><code>apiKey</code></td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. The location of t=
he API key. Valid values are <code>"query"</code>, <code>"header"</code> or=
 <code>"cookie"</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"securitySchemeScheme"></span>scheme</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td><code>http</code></td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. The name of the H=
TTP Authorization scheme to be used in the Authorization header as defined =
in [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spe=
c.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#bib-rfc7235" title=3D"Hypertext Transfer Pro=
tocol (HTTP/1.1): Authentication">RFC7235</a></cite>] <a href=3D"https://da=
tatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7235#section-5.1">Section 5.1</a>.  The valu=
es used <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> be registered in the <cite><a cla=
ss=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/o=
as/v3.0.3.html#bib-iana-http-authschemes" title=3D"Hypertext Transfer Proto=
col (HTTP) Authentication Scheme Registry">IANA Authentication Scheme regis=
try</a></cite>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"securitySchemeBearerFormat"></span>bearerFormat</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td><code>http</code> (<code>"bearer"</code>)</td>
<td>A hint to the client to identify how the bearer token is formatted.  Be=
arer tokens are usually generated by an authorization server, so this infor=
mation is primarily for documentation purposes.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"securitySchemeFlows"></span>flows</td>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3=
.0.3.html#oauth-flows-object">OAuth Flows Object</a></td>
<td><code>oauth2</code></td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. An object contain=
ing configuration information for the flow types supported.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span id=3D"securitySchemeOpenIdConnectUrl"></span>openIdConnectUrl</td=
>
<td style=3D"text-align:center"><code>string</code></td>
<td><code>openIdConnect</code></td>
<td><strong><em class=3D"rfc2119">REQUIRED</em></strong>. OpenId Connect UR=
L to discover OAuth2 configuration values. This <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<=
/em> be in the form of a URL.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>This object <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> be extended with <a href=3D"h=
ttps://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#specification-extensions">Specific=
ation Extensions</a>.</p>
