=3D"header-wrapper"><h4 id=3D"x4-7-30-security-requirement-object"><bdi cla=
ss=3D"secno">4.7.30 </bdi>Security Requirement Object</h4><a class=3D"self-=
link" href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#security-requiremen=
t-object" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.7.30"></a></div>
<p>Lists the required security schemes to execute this operation.
The name used for each property <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> correspond =
to a security scheme declared in the <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/o=
as/v3.0.3.html#componentsSecuritySchemes">Security Schemes</a> under the <a=
 href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#components-object">Compo=
nents Object</a>.</p>
<p>Security Requirement Objects that contain multiple schemes require that =
all schemes <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be satisfied for a request to b=
e authorized.
This enables support for scenarios where multiple query parameters or HTTP =
headers are required to convey security information.</p>
<p>When a list of Security Requirement Objects is defined on the <a href=3D=
"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#openapi-object">OpenAPI Object</=
a> or <a href=3D"https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.3.html#operation-object=
">Operation Object</a>, only one of the Security Requirement Objects in the=
 list needs to be satisfied to authorize the request.</p>
